dcterms:description: The arXiv multiplex network is a collaboration network where each layer represents a different category, i.e. research topic, of the pre-print archive. The network consists of 19310 nodes over 13 layers, connected through 48657 intra-layer connections and 20738 inter-layer ones.
dcterms:title: arXiv

dcterms:creator: C. Stark
B.-J. Breitkreutz
T. Reguly
L. Boucher
A. Breitkreutz
M. Tyers
dcterms:description: This is the protein-genetic interaction multiplex network of the common fruit fly Drosophila melanogaster, where layers correspond to interactions of different nature. The dataset consists of 11867 nodes over 7 layers, with 40228 intra-layer links and 5173 inter-layer ones.
dcterms:title: Drosophila

dcterms:creator: M. E. Dickison
M. Magnani
L. Rossi
dcterms:description: This is a multiplex network obtained from Friendfeed, a social media aggregator, which allows users to register their accounts on other online social networks. The dataset consists of 11827 nodes over 3 layers, with 74815 intra-layer connections and 6028 inter-layer ones.
dcterms:title: ff-tw-yt
